John-Paul Langbroek stands down as the Leader of the Opposition in the Australian state of Queensland with the sitting Lord Mayor of Brisbane Campbell Newman favoured to take his place. (ABC News)Former Premier of the Australian state of Tasmania David Bartlett resigns as a government minister and will resign from the House of Assembly. (AAP via Sydney Morning Herald)The Scottish National Party urges British Prime Minister David Cameron to amend the Scotland Bill to give the Scottish Parliament greater legislative powers. (BBC)